    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-01-24T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-01-24T12:00:00-05:00" n="746"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d746">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 300.115/6783</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-24T17:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 24, 1916, 5 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11.45 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3629. Do not understand reference to porcelain guides in your telegram 2759,
                    January 21.<note n="1" xml:id="d746fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_551">p. 551</ref>.</note> My
                    2443, October 29,<note n="2" xml:id="d746fn2">
                        <ref target="frus1915Supp#pg_264">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1915, Supplement, p.
                        264</ref>.</note> informed you of <pb facs="0853" n="567" xml:id="pg_567"/>
                    Foreign Office statement that permit for 153 cases for
                        <persName>Mitchell</persName>-Bissell would be granted. Since then have
                    heard nothing further about this shipment; so confidently [suppose] guides were
                    received in the United States. Have no record of other guides asked for.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
